# Update PLAN.md on Key Changes

When you make changes that affect **architecture**, **game design**, or **gameplay mechanics**, update `PLAN.md` at the project root to reflect those changes.

## When to Update

- Adding or removing a major system (e.g., new entity type, new UI panel, new manager class)
- Changing how core systems interact (e.g., physics, rendering, inventory flow)
- Adding new block types, item types, or crafting recipes that represent a new feature
- Changing controls or player mechanics
- Adding new biomes, world generation features, or visual systems

## When NOT to Update

- Bug fixes that don't change design
- Code refactors that keep the same behavior
- Minor tweaks to values (e.g., adjusting block hardness or loot weights)

## How to Update

- Edit the relevant phase section in `PLAN.md` or add a new section if it's a new feature
- Keep descriptions concise (1-2 sentences per bullet)
- List key files involved
- Update the Controls Summary table if controls change
